			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin-left: 40px;">The Configuration Control Specialist is responsible for the activities required to implement configuration management (CM) related activities on multiple projects under the direction of the QC/Test Manager.<br /> <br /><strong>Performance Objectives<br /></strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Develop, document, and execute configuration management plans and procedures to effectively identify, manage changes to, and report status of product designs and custom engineering solutions. This function covers both software and hardware issues in a development and production environment.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Implement an automated configuration management system that integrates version control, traceability, tracking, and build management functions.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Conduct and follow up on multiple meetings to ensure that: <br />Required features and fixes are being built into loads according to schedule. <br />Software modification requests are tracked and driven to closure. <br />Hardware issues are documented and driven to closure (non conformances principally). <br />Work orders are created and driven to closure. These issues address production issues according to the production schedule. </p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Create weekly reports tracking progress on hardware and software issues, including close/open rates, average age, late issues, and time to closure. Work with the management team to continue to develop metrics as the process matures and improves. </p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Create software loads across the product line. This includes identifying the modules to be built as well as confirming the sanity of the built load with the Test team.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Coordinate engineering change notices (ECNs) and engineering change proposals (ECPs) with all stakeholders.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Maintain and continually improve automated build processes for hardware and software, ensuring that builds work consistently across products.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Develop and improve the package and production release infrastructure that effectively handles change.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Ensure deployed hardware and software, as well as internal testing environments, meet supported configuration standards.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Coach and mentor the development teams in the published configuration control processes, and ensure that the teams comply with the processes.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Maintain a structured document repository that is efficient, effective, and meets the Company’s quality objectives.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Effectively troubleshoot configuration-related problems in all environments; monitor and report status of configuration management activities.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Experience<br />Experience with quality processes (ISO-9001:2008).</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Ability to develop and implement configuration management plans and instructions.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Dedicated to meeting expectations and requirements of both internal and external customers.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Ability to meet aggressive project timelines, while sustaining high performance and high quality.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Ability to effectively prioritize work, anticipate and proactively identify problems/risks, and develop and apply innovative solutions.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Adaptable to changing priorities and pressures.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Strong organizational and time management skills.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Strong work ethic with the ability to sustain long work hours when necessary.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Formal configuration management training is desired.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">BS degree in a technical field with no less than 5 years professional experience in configuration management.</p>]]></description>
